com.turn.ttorrent.common.protocol

Class PeerMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.turn.ttorrent.common.protocol.PeerMessage
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PeerMessage.BitfieldMessage, PeerMessage.CancelMessage, PeerMessage.ChokeMessage, PeerMessage.HaveMessage, PeerMessage.InterestedMessage, PeerMessage.KeepAliveMessage, PeerMessage.NotInterestedMessage, PeerMessage.PieceMessage, PeerMessage.RequestMessage, PeerMessage.UnchokeMessage

    public abstract class PeerMessage
extends Object
    BitTorrent peer protocol messages representations.

    This class and its *Messages subclasses provide POJO representations of the peer protocol messages, along with easy parsing from an input ByteBuffer to quickly get a usable representation of an incoming message.

    Author:
    mpetazzoni
    See Also:
    BitTorrent peer wire protocol

    • Method Detail

      • getType

      • getData

        public ByteBuffer getData()
        Returns a ByteBuffer backed by the same data as this message.

        This method returns a duplicate of the buffer stored in this PeerMessage object to allow for multiple consumers to read from the same message without conflicting access to the buffer's position, mark and limit.

      • validate

        public PeerMessage validate(SharedTorrent torrent)
                     throws PeerMessage.MessageValidationException
        Validate that this message makes sense for the torrent it's related to.

        This method is meant to be overloaded by distinct message types, where it makes sense. Otherwise, it defaults to true.

        Parameters:
        torrent - The torrent this message is about.
        Throws:
        PeerMessage.MessageValidationException

      • parse

        public static PeerMessage parse(ByteBuffer buffer,
                                SharedTorrent torrent)
                         throws ParseException
        Parse the given buffer into a peer protocol message.

        Parses the provided byte array and builds the corresponding PeerMessage subclass object.

        Parameters:
        buffer - The byte buffer containing the message data.
        torrent - The torrent this message is about.
        Returns:
        A PeerMessage subclass instance.
        Throws:
        ParseException - When the message is invalid, can't be parsed or does not match the protocol requirements.
